│ THOUGHT: Now I can see the issue! In the `processSwitch` function, there's logic that determines if the default destination is unreachable by checking if the constant range of the   │
│ condition covers all possible cases. The problem is in this section:                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ if (!CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)) {                                                                                                                                       │
│   // Mark default dest as unreachable                                                                                                                                                 │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The issue is that `CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)` checks if the constant range size is larger than the number of reachable cases. However, this logic is flawed because it  │
│ doesn't account for the fact that the constant range might include values that aren't explicitly listed as cases but should still go to the default destination.                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ In our test case:                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - The phi node can have values -1 (255) and 0                                                                                                                                         │
│ - The switch has cases for 0, 1, 2                                                                                                                                                    │
│ - So ReachableCaseCount = 1 (only case 0 is reachable based on LVI analysis)                                                                                                          │
