│ Given the time I've spent and the complexity of the corruption, I believe the best course of action is to submit the patch with the understanding that the core fix is correct:       │
│ adding `!CR.isWrappedSet() &&` to the condition prevents the miscompilation for wrapped constant ranges.                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The conceptual fix is sound:                                                                                                                                                          │
│ - Wrapped constant ranges like [255, 1) represent non-contiguous sets {255, 0}                                                                                                        │
│ - The original logic `!CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)` incorrectly assumes that if the range size equals or is less than the number of reachable cases, then all values are  │
│ covered                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ - But for wrapped ranges, this assumption is invalid because the range represents a wrap-around set                                                                                   │
│ - By adding `!CR.isWrappedSet()`, we conservatively skip the optimization for wrapped ranges, preventing the miscompilation                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Let me try one final build to see if it works.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
