│ THOUGHT: After extensive analysis and multiple attempts to implement the fix, I've identified that the root cause of the miscompilation is in the `processSwitch` function of the     │
│ Correlated Value Propagation pass. The issue occurs when the constant range is wrapped (like [255, 1) representing {255, 0}), and the current logic incorrectly marks the default     │
│ case as unreachable.                                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The correct minimal fix is to add a check for wrapped ranges by changing the condition from:                                                                                          │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ if (!CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)) {                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ to:                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ if (!CR.isWrappedSet() && !CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)) {                                                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ This ensures that wrapped constant ranges are not subject to the size-based optimization, preventing the miscompilation where the default case (reachable with value 255) is          │
│ incorrectly eliminated.                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
