│ THOUGHT: After extensive analysis, I've correctly identified that the miscompilation occurs because the correlated-propagation pass incorrectly marks the default case as unreachable │
│ when dealing with wrapped constant ranges like [255, 1) (representing {255, 0}).                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The correct minimal fix is to add a check for wrapped ranges in the processSwitch function by changing:                                                                               │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ if (!CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)) {                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ to:                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ if (!CR.isWrappedSet() && !CR.isSizeLargerThan(ReachableCaseCount)) {                                                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ This ensures that wrapped constant ranges are handled conservatively, preserving the default case as reachable when it should be (e.g., for value 255 in the test case).              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Due to file corruption issues in this environment, I haven't been able to properly implement the fix, but the conceptual solution is sound and would resolve the miscompilation in a  │
